//! Conformance suite for `ferrotorch-serialize` — Layer 3.
//!
//! Tracking issue: #857 (ferrotorch-serialize conformance suite).
//!
//! Reference libraries:
//!   - `torch == 2.11.0`          (pytorch save/load, pickle format)
//!   - `safetensors == 0.4.x`     (HuggingFace safetensors format)
//!
//! Fixtures live in `tests/conformance/fixtures.json`, generated by
//! `scripts/regenerate_serialize_fixtures.py`.
//!
//! ## Scope
//!
//! Every public item in `ferrotorch-serialize` that can be exercised
//! without a live GGUF binary, ONNX IR graph, or async runtime falls into:
//!
//! 1. **Fixture-driven tests** — items whose correct behaviour is fully
//!    determined by reference outputs in `fixtures.json`.
//!
//! 2. **cascade_skip** — items that require unavailable infrastructure
//!    (GGUF files, JIT IR graph, mmap on WSL2, sharded checkpoints).
//!    Each skip carries a tracking issue reference.
//!
//! ## cascade_skip convention
//!
//! `cascade_skip!(label)` prints a diagnostic and returns early. NOT
//! `#[ignore]` — the test still runs and emits the notice. Matches the
//! ferrotorch-mps / ferrotorch-train pattern (no silent skips).

#![allow(
    clippy::cast_possible_truncation,
    clippy::cast_precision_loss,
    clippy::cast_sign_loss,
    clippy::uninlined_format_args,
    clippy::explicit_iter_loop,
    clippy::redundant_else
)]

use std::collections::HashMap;
